# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
#  Transient / build artifacts
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.ipynb_checkpoints/
~$*                      # Office lock/temp files (e.g. ~$Lab Notes.docx)

# Generated outputs (regenerable from source — not tracked)
*.png
*.csv

# Per-source .bib stubs dropped into Sources/ are merged into the top-level
# references.bib — keep them local, don't commit duplicates of the bibliography.
Sources/**/*.bib

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
#  PDFs: ignored by default, then public source documents re-included
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
#  Policy: only PUBLIC documents live in the repo. Government / regulatory
#  / ISO / stakeholder documents are public and tracked. Copyrighted
#  academic papers and books are NOT committed — find them via the `url`
#  field in references.bib (author sites, FERC eLibrary, caiso.com, etc.).
#  Generated PDFs (figures, the built LaTeX notes) stay ignored.
*.pdf

# -- Public documents: tracked --
!Sources/ferc-orders/*.pdf
!Sources/ferc-filings-and-iso-policy/*.pdf
!Sources/msc-opinions/*.pdf
!Sources/stakeholder-comments/*.pdf
!Sources/institutional-context/PGP+Organized+Market+Retrospective+Full+Report.pdf
!Sources/institutional-context/november22_2005jointcomments-iso_rtocouncilregardingfercnoiindocketno_rm05-25-000.pdf

# The lab's own Lab Notes are NOT published yet — keep every format
# (.md / .docx / .pdf) out of the public repo until the lab is ready:
Sources/Lab Notes - Congestion Revenue Allocation.*

# -- Open-access academic (CC BY) — safe to commit --
!Sources/academic-literature/Kiesling - governing the grid - S1744137426100423.pdf

# -- Copyrighted academic material: link-only (see `url` in references.bib) --
#  Sources/academic-literature/* and the O'Neill et al. Elsevier chapter
#  stay ignored. Some are freely posted by their authors and MAY be
#  redistributable; uncommenting a line below includes that PDF — that is
#  the lab's redistribution decision to make, source by source:
# !Sources/academic-literature/flow0800r.pdf
# !Sources/academic-literature/Joskow-MerchantTransmissionInvestment-2005.pdf
# !Sources/academic-literature/JOSKOW-Lessons Learned From Electricity Market Liberalization.pdf
# !Sources/academic-literature/The Competitive Effects of Transmission Capacity in a Deregulated Electricity Industry.pdf
# !Sources/academic-literature/HOGAN-contract network -BF00133621.pdf
#  Always link-only (paywalled, no open author version):
#    Sources/academic-literature/HOGAN-PrimerTransmissionBenefits-2018.pdf
#    Sources/institutional-context/IndependentSystemOperators-...-main.pdf  (Elsevier)

